The paper deals with reasoning under uncertainty, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of sets of desirable gambles is a tool for reasoning with partial probability assessments, which is also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves mathematical formulas and properties, which suggests it could fit into the information theory (cs.IT) or discrete mathematics (cs.DS) categories. Finally, the paper mentions the implementation of these tools in computer programs, which could fall under the category of mathematical software (cs.MA).
